# .gitignore for papers/jss_2026
#
# Policy:
#   COMMITTED  - the harness source (code, config, tests), the public
#                reproduction data inputs, and, inside paper/, only the LaTeX
#                build and its inputs: article.tex, article.pdf, jss.cls,
#                jss.bst, jsslogo.jpg, refs.bib, and the figures the manuscript
#                embeds via \includegraphics.
#   IGNORED    - regenerable run outputs, every figure the manuscript does not
#                embed, the replication bundle, editorial correspondence, and
#                LaTeX/Python build detritus.
#
# A reviewer can clone, run replicate.py, and reproduce every result. The
# inputs and the embedded figures are tracked so the paper compiles from a
# fresh clone without first running the pipeline.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# LaTeX build detritus  (article.pdf is TRACKED - see below)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.aux
*.bbl
*.blg
*.log
*.out
*.toc
*.lof
*.lot
*.fls
*.fdb_latexmk
*.synctex.gz
*.nav
*.snm
*.vrb
build_test.*

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Python build / cache detritus
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.coverage
*.egg-info/
build/
dist/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Regenerable run outputs and the replication bundle
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Study outputs, regenerated by the simulation/application scripts.
simulations/results/
simulations/results_calibrated/
# The replication bundle is a build output of make_replication_zip.py.
factorlasso_jss_replication.zip

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Editorial correspondence stays out of the public repository.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
paper/jss_report/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# paper/ holds the LaTeX build only. The scripts live one level up, in
# papers/jss_2026/. Anything else that lands in paper/ is ignored.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
paper/*.py
paper/*.md
paper/*.csv
paper/*.txt

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# paper/figures/: track only what the build reads. article.tex embeds four
# graphics (usage_signs_heatmap, prior_sensitivity_sweep, tau_sweep,
# etf_credit_beta_vs_lambda), and the repository README embeds
# etf_credit_beta_vs_lambda.png. Every other artefact the scripts emit into
# this directory is regenerable.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
paper/figures/*
!paper/figures/usage_signs_heatmap.pdf
!paper/figures/prior_sensitivity_sweep.pdf
!paper/figures/tau_sweep.pdf
!paper/figures/etf_credit_beta_vs_lambda.pdf
!paper/figures/etf_credit_beta_vs_lambda.png

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Explicitly TRACKED despite living near generated content
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Public reproduction data inputs (yfinance-built ETF panel + factor NAVs).
# These are NOT licensed and ARE committed so reproduction runs from a clone.
!applications/data/
!applications/data/etf_excess_logreturns.csv
!applications/data/futures_risk_factors.csv
!applications/data/riskfree_monthly.csv

# The compiled paper PDF is shipped for reader/reviewer convenience.
# (Remove the '!' line to stop tracking it.)
!paper/article.pdf

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# JSS style files. The journal distributes these in jss-article-tex.zip from
# https://www.jstatsoft.org/style, and they are not a TeX Live package. They
# are not our content, so we do not redistribute them. They stay on disk, so
# the paper compiles locally and the replication bundle stays self-contained.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
paper/jss.cls
paper/jss.bst
paper/jsslogo.jpg
